reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great storage device at a good proce range
reviews.reviewText: I have this for data transfer between my Surface tablet and computer. It is fast, reliable, and well constructed. Feels solid and do not take too much space. In fact, it goes in any pocket of my bag. Glad I choose this one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Small and fast
reviews.reviewText: Excellent performance and great size. Works great with my MacBook Air M1.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent size and functionality
reviews.reviewText: I bought the drive as a mechanism to back up the hard drives on multiple computers, It comes with adapters for USB A and C drives and is rapid with data transfer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works on everything except iPhones
reviews.reviewText: Bought it a couple of days ago, expecting to be able to download all the photos and videos from my iPhone to the drive to clear up some space, despite using an Apple Original USB-C to Lightning cable, and also a USB to Lightning Adapter neither could get the drive to show up. I even tested another USB drive and it worked so idk why this one doesn't.Anyway, aside from that one quirk, the drive works like a dream. It's super small and ultraportable, doesn't overheat even when transferring 50+ gigabytes of files to it, and the included USB to USB-C adapter is a nice touch to take advantage of C's greater transfer speed. There is literally nothing like it I could find on amazon in the same price point, and it works really well so I'd 100% recommend to everyone except iPhone users, but it does work fine with Macs so idk what's up with that.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My two work well as backup drives.
reviews.reviewText: Installed two to back up my computer with Acronis. One is set to backup on Tuesday and the other is set to back up on Saturday. So far so good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Does not work
reviews.reviewText: Does not work on any device any usb port, any OS.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars 1 TB USB Drive.
reviews.reviewText: I use it to back up GoPro video after editing on my laptop computer. It does what it says it will do and I haven’t had any problems with it. USB 3 is plenty fast compared to 2.0. The case is rugged enough for every day use. I would recommend it to anyone and I would buy it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I copied around 130 gb to this drive in the time it took to close a few screen windows and check back. Like, well under five minutes. I didn't time it exactly, but it's USB C speed for sure.Compare that to an alleged USB C flash drive -> 45 gb took hours. Excruciating,The drive comes in an enclosure at the price of a bare drive. That's key, because I am so tired of having to break out the tiny screwdrivers when I'm looking for files. The enclosure itself is good quality and stays cool. It also comes with a USBC to USB 3 cable with an adapter back to USBC.Would definitely buy again.

Funciona bien.Esta unidad es bonita, compacta y funciona bien. Acabo de probar su velocidad en mi Mac M1, que mostró 362 MB/s de escritura y 328 MB/s de lectura. Esto está en un rango similar al de mis otros SSD. Sí, no son los discos rápidos que existen, pero son adecuados para mis necesidades.
Ausschlaggebend für den Kauf waren die Speichergröße, Größe und Gewicht. Über die Lebensdauer gibt es noch keine Info, nur deshalb vier Sterne.
